bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"b8634f7113bda23ed66d15be338c7c07eeb16f600f86c7afd43024bb36d28d59","event_uuid":"a9510854-57de-48bf-a1bd-62a30c2eed9a","position":{"commit_sha":"a0d978dd6378443b61d20fac281f7f13a7b17bf5","position":"1784747776327587001-a9510854-57de-48bf-a1bd-62a30c2eed9a"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"35dd40616547b6829c3e8f3ae48c28130e01153e976799921f3722080b5ca16c","event_uuid":"67a5ecc9-0f79-4616-835f-eb72ca1ee84e","position":{"commit_sha":"0b3f752404d62b74cf6a555b5e06bcbb89f0ebca","position":"1784751226351563001-67a5ecc9-0f79-4616-835f-eb72ca1ee84e"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"2fcad746d0519fd6e9ec40b7d6365b9fc6ace6c49227e788237b5fbe48a70e8f","event_uuid":"1cba338d-49f8-4120-ad05-e151d8c03629","position":{"commit_sha":"665394fdd29b8e886a1f2ff28f046c4bd93069ba","position":"1784751345605397001-1cba338d-49f8-4120-ad05-e151d8c03629"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":null,"claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":null,"comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Pre-review interface correction from upstream 75de finding ffe785ed3182f1edc: call the existing attest.compute_validity with profile=CLOSE; do not introduce compute_plan_review_validity. This child will still receive its own sequential review later.","timestamp":1784547088365841001},{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"First review BLOCK remediation: accepted f2c30288c7d7b7455/f405a4d3989ff5035 by explicitly making certified 75de/5967 interfaces implementation prerequisites and naming their delivered CLOSE/profile/phase contracts. Accepted fe5da54264f77dc5d/ffbe76fafcffb6f75 by adding a generic pre_status_check callback to txn.transition_core, invoked inside the existing lock immediately before STATUS append; close passes the pure gate closure and never double-locks. Added the exact CLOSE rationale, verdict/remediation/exception vocabulary, default-off AC, config schema mechanics, exemptions, advanced docs, concrete tests, and existing ordering-test impacts. Rerunning before downstream review.","timestamp":1784558399874666001},{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Plan-review advisory dispositions: accept f6307f74a5d63abf0; implementation verification will use the existing tests/unit/test_config_surface_golden.py (already covered by file impact). Accept f7a8955e9077c2598; unexpected unavailable results will emit structured WARNING plan_review_close_gate_unavailable. For f8c0593b5fec33d5f and f7ff4327b700ef822, retain the generic transaction-local pre_status_check callback: it is the minimal seam that executes higher-level close policy inside the existing single lock without coupling txn.py to plan-review logic; document this advanced transaction/concurrency extension point during implementation. f607dd457c67f9209 is non-blocking acceptance-criteria style feedback.","timestamp":1784559254755588001},{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Implementation and held-out validation complete locally. Added default-off CLOSE plan gate, exact remediation, pre-completion ordering, under-lock recheck, zero-network local read context, config surface, and advanced docs. TDD: 21 intended RED failures initially; implementer saw only 2 happy tests; held-out first run 22/22 GREEN; callback mutation produced 2 expected RED failures; zero-network gap was RED then corrected on same standard tier; final close oracle 26 tests plus focused suite 167/167 GREEN. make check PASS; broad xdist non-integration suite 6921 passed, 28 skipped. Standard-tier worker used 2 implementation iterations.","timestamp":1784751226351563001},{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Implementation reviewed at Gerrit change 894: https://rebar.solutions.navateam.com/c/rebar/+/894 (commit 880cc2c8c80f829461692611d3febc00de8ebb39). RED-first held-out oracle reached 22/22 GREEN, mutation checks caught the race and zero-network defects, focused suite 167 passed, make check passed, and broad non-integration suite passed. Awaiting LLM-Review +1 and Verified +1 before submit and close.","timestamp":1784751345605397001}],"created_at":1784517369436374001,"creation_channel":"python","deps":[{"link_uuid":"d81d6b9b-df07-4449-984f-f1e7f0c206f6","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"75de-02b0-d454-410b"},{"link_uuid":"a5086362-47bb-4981-88bc-61fa66f43e07","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"5967-4476-7f9f-442d"}],"description":"# Add the close-time plan-review gate\n\n## Goal\nPrevent an implemented ticket from closing after its own plan or a pinned upstream plan changed during execution, without running plan review inside close or invalidating every implementation because implementation files changed.\n\n## Implementation\n- This story is implemented only after its declared dependencies: 75de supplies `PlanValidityProfile.CLOSE`, `compute_validity(..., profile=...)`, pin health/enforcement, and additive validity results; 5967 supplies signed review phase/floor and phase compatibility. Those interfaces are feature-branch deliverables and are not present on current main before the predecessors land. Do not wire close until both predecessor implementations are available.\n- Register `require_plan_review_for_close: bool = False` on `_config_schema.py::VerifyConfig`, add the bool coercer to `_SECTIONS[\"verify\"]`, and update the config-surface golden. Default false preserves every existing close path and performs no signature or plan-material reads.\n- Add `_commands/gates.py::close_plan_review_gate_check(ticket_id, ticket_state, *, repo_root) -> dict` as the sole close policy boundary. It calls `signing.verify_signature(kind=\"plan-review\")`, then 75de's `compute_validity(..., kind=\"plan-review\", profile=PlanValidityProfile.CLOSE)`. CLOSE intentionally disables only code freshness (verified HEAD and per-file dependency hashes) because implementation changes are expected during execution; signature, reopen, registry, current own material, 5967 phase compatibility, and configured pin enforcement remain active. This cannot reuse `claim_gate_check`, because DEFAULT intentionally blocks code drift while CLOSE must not.\n- The helper runs only when `verify.require_plan_review_for_close=true` and the ticket is a task/story/epic taking the normal close path. It returns `{ok, verdict, reason}` and never invokes a model or network. `verify.enforce_plan_material_pins` controls only whether pin health invalidates; phase incompatibility, own-material drift, reopen, registry, signature, and malformed metadata always invalidate. Any unexpected local read/parser/signature exception is caught and returned fail-closed as verdict `unavailable`.\n- In `transition_close.close_ticket`, after structural/exemption/force checks and before `_completion_precheck`, reduce current state and call `close_plan_review_gate_check`. Failure raises the normal command error before completion verification with exact message `plan-review close gate: <verdict>: <reason>. Run rebar review-plan <canonical-id> separately, then retry close.` The verdict is the exact `compute_validity` verdict (`unsigned`, `stale-reopened`, `stale-regver`, `stale-material`, `unverifiable-material`, `stale-pin-drift`, `stale-pin-missing`, `malformed-pin`, `incompatible-phase`, `malformed-phase`, or `unavailable`); reason is diagnostic only. Close never launches `review-plan` itself.\n- Extend `txn.transition_core(..., *, pre_status_check: Callable[[Mapping[str, Any]], None] | None = None)` as a generic local pre-append hook; every existing caller defaults `None`. After acquiring the existing global write lock, re-reading state, verifying expected status, and applying structural close rules—but immediately before appending STATUS—invoke the callback with that freshly reduced state. A raised `RebarError` aborts the transaction and releases the lock without append/commit. `txn.py` imports no plan-review code.\n- When close enforcement applies, `close_ticket` passes a closure as `pre_status_check`; the closure calls the same pure `close_plan_review_gate_check` on the locked fresh state and raises the same command error on failure. This is the second check, not pre-existing txn behavior. It runs inside the single existing critical section; `close_ticket` never acquires a second lock. A signature, ticket, phase, own-material, or related-pin change between precheck and lock is therefore caught before STATUS append.\n- Preserve existing scope and bypass rules: bugs, session logs, code reviews, identities, and idea→closed remain exempt exactly as the claim gate; a non-empty force-close reason bypasses both completion verification and this plan-review gate and retains its audit event; structural child-closure rules are never bypassed. `close_ticket` remains the sole production task/story/epic close entry point, and all CLI/library/MCP surfaces inherit the behavior.\n- Document the CLOSE profile policy, flag interaction, error/remediation vocabulary, locked callback, and force/exemption behavior in advanced `docs/plan-review-gate.md`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] With `require_plan_review_for_close=false` or absent, normal close behavior is byte-for-byte equivalent and performs no plan-review reads.\n- [ ] With enforcement enabled, task/story/epic close runs the plan gate before completion verification.\n- [ ] CLOSE accepts certified, registry-current, material-current, phase-compatible reviews despite HEAD or file-dependency drift.\n- [ ] Unsigned, reopened, stale-registry, own-material drift, malformed metadata, and phase incompatibility block even when pin enforcement is false.\n- [ ] Pin drift/missing/malformed blocks only when `enforce_plan_material_pins=true`; disabled enforcement remains advisory.\n- [ ] Every failure uses the exact verdict-prefixed message and separate `review-plan` remediation; unexpected exceptions fail closed as `unavailable` without traceback.\n- [ ] Close performs zero plan-review LLM/model/network calls.\n- [ ] The generic `pre_status_check` runs under the existing lock after fresh state/structural checks and before STATUS append.\n- [ ] A failing locked callback appends and commits no STATUS event.\n- [ ] A plan/signature/phase/material/pin change between precheck and lock is rejected by the locked recheck.\n- [ ] Existing transition callers that omit `pre_status_check` are unchanged.\n- [ ] Bugs, session logs, code reviews, identities, and idea→closed retain their existing exemptions.\n- [ ] Non-empty force-close reason bypasses both gates with the existing audit trail but never bypasses structural child closure.\n- [ ] `docs/plan-review-gate.md` documents the CLOSE policy, both flags, callback ordering, error vocabulary, and bypass scope.\n\n## Verification\n- `pytest -q tests/unit/test_plan_review_close_gate.py` proves the full validity/verdict/config matrix, code-drift exclusion, fail-closed exceptions, and zero-model behavior.\n- `pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_plan_review_gate.py tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_completion_gate.py` proves precheck ordering, public close behavior, default-off compatibility, and remediation messages.\n- `pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_transition_pre_status_check.py` proves inside-lock ordering, race rejection, and no-write callback failure.\n- `pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_idea_close_bypass.py tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_attested_signing.py` updates existing exemption/force/signing ordering assertions.\n- `pytest -q tests/unit/test_plan_review_docs.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_config_surface.py` proves advanced documentation and config registration/golden coverage.\n- Run `make check` and the full non-LLM test suite.\n","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/_commands/gates.py","reason":"Expose the CLOSE-profile plan-review gate helper."},{"path":"src/rebar/_commands/transition_close.py","reason":"Run pre-completion check and pass the locked callback."},{"path":"src/rebar/_commands/transition.py","reason":"Preserve close outcomes and force/exemption behavior."},{"path":"src/rebar/_commands/txn.py","reason":"Add the generic inside-lock pre-STATUS callback."},{"path":"src/rebar/_config_schema.py","reason":"Register optional close-gate config and coercer."},{"path":"tests/golden/config_surface.json","reason":"Record verify.require_plan_review_for_close."},{"path":"docs/plan-review-gate.md","reason":"Document CLOSE policy, callback, errors, and bypass scope."},{"path":"tests/unit/test_plan_review_close_gate.py","reason":"Prove validity matrix, code-drift exclusion, failures, and zero-model behavior."},{"path":"tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_plan_review_gate.py","reason":"Verify public close behavior and remediation."},{"path":"tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_completion_gate.py","reason":"Update and verify gate ordering."},{"path":"tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_transition_pre_status_check.py","reason":"Prove inside-lock ordering and no-write failure."},{"path":"tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_idea_close_bypass.py","reason":"Update exemption and ordering assertions."},{"path":"tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_attested_signing.py","reason":"Update verify-close-sign ordering assertions."},{"path":"tests/unit/test_plan_review_docs.py","reason":"Verify advanced CLOSE documentation."},{"path":"tests/interfaces/contracts/test_config_surface.py","reason":"Verify config registration and defaults."}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","5967-4476-7f9f-442d"],["depends_on","75de-02b0-d454-410b"],["parent","jira-reb-1160"]],"parent_id":"jira-reb-1160","parent_status_uuid":"3fb77ede-2966-4a89-8e45-d162d6f2752f","plan_review_phase":"execution","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["plan-review","jira-reb-1160"],"ticket_id":"2bbd-87f6-8765-4b00","ticket_type":"story","title":"Require a separately attested current plan review at close","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["0d579ee0-ed93-44fe-8fd3-3419cea887b3","1ce6fd4b-7825-497c-92b2-60b7cb5054b8","d81d6b9b-df07-4449-984f-f1e7f0c206f6","a5086362-47bb-4981-88bc-61fa66f43e07","be319c8a-ccc1-4c35-b9ee-d4ed0e70e1f2","b63a2f91-c096-4a8b-84a4-ec215c4341b3","eb69047a-cf0d-42eb-9d95-e8982781f7f7","b182c6fe-21f2-4ebd-9523-2c798db43e79","e959e6df-4139-4439-a87c-4ec0edea7fc0","ae81e8fd-4992-416c-82ab-72572b837f62","ac8a7f3e-bb87-480a-9a2d-ea84f39e8404","0f8b0e65-1904-4ddc-be87-f7c96ed163ad","2a4cd89f-f47f-4733-a819-0dc7009d8fef","1d3b0e2b-8b40-4e65-a275-1e4cf2365e2d","12e5099c-93de-4c7f-ad13-252f65db15ee","3fb77ede-2966-4a89-8e45-d162d6f2752f","a9510854-57de-48bf-a1bd-62a30c2eed9a","67a5ecc9-0f79-4616-835f-eb72ca1ee84e","1cba338d-49f8-4120-ad05-e151d8c03629"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784751345605397002,"uuid":"a286d1a3-c75e-4a89-978a-0001ad5c2dcd"}